# Supabase Configuration (Client-side safe)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key

# Server-side only keys - NEVER prefix with VITE_
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_supabase_service_role_key

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================
# 
# 1. GROQ_API_KEY and SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY must NEVER be prefixed with VITE_ 
#    (VITE_ prefix exposes variables to the client bundle)
#
# 2. SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY bypasses Row Level Security (RLS)
#    - Only use this in server-side code (api/ folder)
#    - Never import this in src/ folder
#    - Get this from: Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API → service_role key
#
# 3. Before deploying to production, update ALLOWED_ORIGINS in api/ai-search.ts
#    to match your actual domain(s)
#
# 4. The Supabase anon key is safe for client-side use because:
#    - Row Level Security (RLS) is enabled on all tables
#    - Users can only access their own data via auth.uid() checks
#
# 5. Rate limits are configured in api/ai-search.ts:
#    - 10 requests/minute per IP
#    - 3 requests/5s burst limit
#    - 500 requests/day global cap
